the stitches over the area where the bone had to be removed to extract the tooth constrict movement ability in the jaw leading to serious throbbing pain trying to get normal jaw movement again after the surgery taking a lot of pain relief to be able to control it.

i have had severe jaw pain as the stitches from wisdom tooth surgery have almost dissolved and getting complications from issues with the nerve injury. finally after 4 doses of immediate release palexia in a short time, a total of 200mg the pain is under control.

once i had the first tablet of palexia ir yesterday afternoon two days after surgery i knew that i was well enough to go the cinema today 3 days after the surgery and has substantially reduced the disabling impact of the pain that was previously left uncontrolled.

tapentadol is not a pro drug so does not require metabolism by the liver via the cyp2d6 enzyme to be active like codeine and tramadol do and start to feel it within only a few minutes, being active from when taken, ir cut in half of 50mg, 25mg is still very strong.

the noradrenaline component of the tapentadol is useful for situations with rapidly increasing severe pain levels, the palexia immediate release is able to treat hypotension quickly as well as relieving pain along with the strong opiate effect on pain receptors.

i passed out for 4 hours on friday night due to escalating extreme nerve pain in my jaw & had gone into a neurogenic shock syndrome that can cause dangerous and life threatening hypotension, i woke up late in the 2nd half of broncos v storm then had seen the score.

the wisdom tooth caused damage to my inferior alveolar nerve well before the surgery to remove the tooth and instead of being numb for 3-4 weeks as the oral surgeon thought it would be, it is the complete opposite and has caused very severe and unexpected jaw pain.

i am now on palexia 50mg in the immediate release version after my jaw and mouth opening had muscular paralysis due to excruciating pain and was a big struggle to be able to eat much, 2 tablets of panadeine forte was a lot less effective on it compared to palexia.

wisdom tooth surgery had complications with the roots of the tooth entangled in my inferior alveolar nerve and had cut off blood supply from under the gum to my right cheek so was delicate to do. recovery will take weeks for the numbness and nerve pain to ease.

when i used tapentadol in 2018 i found that my immune system worked well for very severe pain where anti-biotics (augmentin duo forte) were required due to severe strep infection so could be presumed to have minimal impact on immune health as with tramadol.

tapentadol is a newer drug so it wasn't included in the data i was looking at but is quite similar to tramadol in terms of being like an antidepressant but less seritonin & has a strong opioid effect a bit similar to oxycodone but with far less severe side effects.

tramadol along with oxycodone and buprenorphine have minimal impact on the immune system, while methadone, fentanyl, codeine and pethidine moderately impact immune health, with morphine causing significant immune suppression.

morphine has a lot of issues with immune suppression, making the dilaudid immediate release hydromorphone a better option for severe pain after the wisdom tooth removal surgery as it has a more limited impact on the immune system and less risk of getting infection.

slow release tablets are good for lesser severe pain during the day, whereas the oral liquids react much more quickly to control very severe pain or induce sleep than even immediate release tablets with metabolism and similar to morphine being given via iv drip.

oxynorm oral liquid is 1st line for severe short term post surgical severe pain even though its more potent than the base strength ordine which is designated as 2nd line along with the hydromorphone dilaudid, this will be something for my anesthetist to consider.

an anomaly that occurs in revised pbs for opioids, short term severe pain post surgery the pbs prefers oxycodone for the worst of 1st line pain, over morphine which i cannot tolerate well at all so would have a choice of morphine or hydromorphone 2nd line instead.

the biala appointments with dr jeremy hayllar in 2 month intervals, so would book in again for early august which is the time interval for which starts requiring the medicines regulation and quality registration with queensland health for the schedule 8's.

as half life for hydromorphone is 2 to 3 hours so can last in pre, during and post surgical phase for pain relief. it is highly likely given my current insomnia issues with only mild to moderate pain, i will need to use it to sleep easily also after the surgery.

not suitably able to use iv fentanyl during a relatively short surgical procedure to get the wisdom tooth out due to its problem with receptor activity in the brain causing issues with temporal lobe, hydromorphone is an alternative weaker than analogue alfentanil.

the qld border closure could very well be challenged in the high court because of its cost to trade and impacted businesses may try and make the state government foot the bill for lost trade in the state. it would also be discriminatory to favour certain states.

section 117 - "a subject of the queen, resident in any state, shall not be subject in any other state to any disability or discrimination which would not be equally applicable to him if he were a subject of the queen resident in such other state."

section 92 - trade within the commonwealth to be free: "on the imposition of uniform duties of customs, trade, commerce, and intercourse among the states, whether by means of internal carriage or ocean navigation, shall be absolutely free."

the state border restrictions being maintained for too long does make them vulnerable to be eventually constitutionally challenged. section 92 is one: trade within the commonwealth to be free, while section 117: rights of residents in states is another.
